{"kind":"comment","edges":[{"type":"on","target":{"kind":"note","ref":"mai-cokf"}}],"body":"## Goal\nmai auto-pushes notes to a configured remote after every write, with blocked-hosts safety and cat_sort_uniq merge on conflict.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Engine pushes refs/notes/maitake after Create and Append when remote is configured\n- [ ] Push only to explicitly configured remote (no default)\n- [ ] Blocked hosts list prevents push to github.com etc\n- [ ] On push rejection: fetch + cat_sort_uniq merge + retry (using git-appraise PullNotes/MergeNotes)\n- [ ] Push failures warn to stderr, don't block the write\n- [ ] mai sync-init \u003cremote\u003e configures the remote\n- [ ] mai sync does manual fetch + merge + push\n- [ ] Config in .maitake/config (remote, blocked-hosts)\n\n## Verification\n- [ ] Create note with remote configured → note appears on remote\n- [ ] Push to blocked host → warning, no push\n- [ ] Two machines diverge → cat_sort_uniq merge resolves correctly\n- [ ] Push failure → write still succeeds, warning shown\n\n## Worktree\n- .\n\n","timestamp":"2026-03-28T15:12:46Z","branch":"main"}
